    <main>
      <h2>New Clothes</h2>

      <p>I don't quite fit the dress's seams<br>
	These lines of fabric tug and pull<br>
	At tender places, and reveal<br>
	The shapes I'd rather not see
      </p>

      <p>The top of my figure is a little small<br>
	And leaves an awkward space<br>
	Between outsize expectations<br>
	And the actual thing,
      </p>

      <p>The jawline on my face.<br>
	Struggling I twist and turn into<br>
	My expected role, contorting<br>
	Through unreasonable threads
      </p>

      <p>The same way that I bend my vowels<br>
	And jam up rising tones<br>
	Trying to move my lips in grace<br>
	Given the sounds of another's speech
      </p>

      <p>To make something I can call my own</p>

      <p>I've stumbled in wearing heels and<br>
	Tripped in writing songs,<br>
	Only finding my feet when I found<br>
	The feminine has many accents
      </p>

      <p>And different does not mean wrong.</p>
      
